      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly specified in ASTM F1717 and are the quantities used in the 510(k) submission to characterise construct mechanical performance. Clinical relevance established: construct stiffness correlates with load sharing at the fusion site; yield force bounds the onset of permanent deformation. Gradation 2 achieved: QoI-to-COU relevance mapping documented."
